<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <ol>
            <li>On the left side of the interface, click <b>Users</b>.</li>
            <li>In the grid, click the name of the user.</li>
            <li>On the left side of the dialog, click <b>Permissions</b>.</li>
            <li>
                <p>From the <span class="Emphasis">Level</span> field, select either <span class="Emphasis">Global Permissions</span> or choose the name of a specific project. <span class="topic-only">In order to see projects in the drop-down, the user must be assigned to them (see </span><MadCap:xref href="../../../../Central/Users/Main-Activities/Associating-Users-Teams-Projects.htm" class="topic-only">Assigning Users to Teams and Projects</MadCap:xref><span class="topic-only">).</span></p>
                <div class="topic-only">
                    <MadCap:snippetBlock src="Note-Global-Permissions.flsnp" />
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Select any of the check boxes to give the user the appropriate permissions in the system.</p>
                <div class="topic-only">
                    <MadCap:snippetBlock src="Permissions-List.flsnp" />
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>Click <span class="Emphasis">Save</span>.</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>